Energy as an essential resource, not only plays a pivotal role in the growth of human well-being and socioeconomic development (
                     Verma et al., 2021
                     ), but also profoundly affects and depends on the natural environment due to the complexity of its provision and consumption (
                     Fuso Nerini et al., 2018
                     ). With the concern on energy poverty (
                     González-Eguino, 2015) and global warming associated with unprecedented extreme weather events (Reichstein et al., 2021), the exigencies of promoting energy sustainability have gained soaring attention.
